content_vision: I am a secret agent. I'll stop crime and try to get the Mr. Evil.
text:
Verse 1:
brraaat! that's the sound of the gun,
poppa never showed us love, we forget those days and move on.
we conquered it all, ruled every inch of land
but i'm not a child, my ego demands.
you gotta be an angel from above, an odyssey so pristine,
time to get up, rise and shine, on that grind once more, so keen,
oh oui baby, let's go, take the world, it's our scene.
don't wanna get caught, gotta run away,

Pre-Chorus 1:
and even though you try to deceive your own heart,
maybe runnin' around ain't gonna lead to a fresh start.

Chorus 1:
be aware of the owner, that's me, don't forget,
future, let 'em know who's the real threat,
you gets no lovin' from me, you just bringin' regret.
show me how you move it, make me go wild,

Verse 2:
we can start over, come back like it's new,
but you want to play, better watch out, the real owner's coming through.
under the cooled jeweled moon, we dance all night,
can't afford to lose them, they're the ones that make us feel all right.
been lost in the flames, but i ain't gon' fold,
still fightin' for my soul, i'm tryna break the mold.
sipping on champagne, eating lobster meals,
wake up, you need to open your eyes and feel,

Chorus 2:
and even though you fool your soul, they still look at each other like they're whole.
two niggas run up on me, tryna act tough,
but fuck baby, they bolt like lightning when i pull out my stuff.
i'm counting my cash, yeah i stack up,

Bridge:
your girl's wildin' out, she's on that crippin',
but don't worry, i'll take care of her, 'cause i'm the slickest dancer in the building,
and at the end of the night, we'll settle for some two potato fries.
free from the struggle, my young niggas take flight,

Outro:
feeling so fly, yeah oh yeah yeah
flowing like yung lean, can't nobody stop me.

Solo:
cause he say i ride real good, yeah that's what they all say,
hari telah tiba di penghujungnya, it's time to slay,

Instrumental:
these girls chasin' paper like it's a bullfight,
ain't got time to chat, got too much on my mind tonight.

active_struct.name: The Epic Saga
attrs: utilizes multiple instrumental sections (intro, bridge, and solo) to add variety and showcase musical talents
allows for variations in the verses (V1, V2) and choruses (C1, C2)
provides a strong and dynamic outro with an instrumental solo (S)
suitable for songs that focus heavily on instrumentation and musicianship

struct_suggs.name: The Dynamic Build
attrs: follows a traditional verse-chorus-bridge-chorus structure
allows for a buildup in energy and emotion throughout the song, with a strong outro
provides room for a dynamic instrumental section (bridge)
suitable for songs with a straightforward message or story

struct_suggs.name: The Wave of Emotion
attrs: includes a prechorus, adding a sense of anticipation and buildup before the chorus
allows for variations and repetitions in the verse and chorus sections
offers room for an instrumental section (intro and outro)
suitable for songs with a strong chorus and build-up in energy

struct_suggs.name: The Instrumental Journey
attrs: has a strong and unique intro (I) followed by a verse (V1) and chorus (C1)
includes a standout instrumental theme melody (T) and a bridge (B)
provides room for a second verse (V2) and chorus (C2) before returning to the original chorus (C1) in the outro (O)
suitable for songs with a catchy melody and a memorable instrumental theme

struct_suggs.name: The Epic Saga
attrs: utilizes multiple instrumental sections (intro, bridge, and solo) to add variety and showcase musical talents
allows for variations in the verses (V1, V2) and choruses (C1, C2)
provides a strong and dynamic outro with an instrumental solo (S)
suitable for songs that focus heavily on instrumentation and musicianship

struct_suggs.name: The Shift in Perspective
attrs: offers a non-traditional structure by starting with a verse first (V1) instead of an intro (I)
includes a prechorus (PC1) before the first chorus (C1)
allows for a varied buildup with an instrumental bridge (B)
suitable for songs that want to deviate from the traditional verse-chorus-bridge structure

struct_suggs.name: The Intricate Dance
attrs: incorporates a prechorus (PC1 and PC2) in between each verse (V1 and V2), increasing the intensity of the song
utilizes an instrumental theme melody (T) in both the intro (I) and the outro (O)
includes a bridge (B) to provide a dynamic change in the song
suitable for songs that want to build up and maintain energy throughout

struct_suggs.name: The Unpredictable Jam
attrs: utilizes a prechorus (PC1 and PC2) to build up before the chorus (C1 and C2)
provides a strong instrumental section (intro and solo) to showcase musical abilities
includes a bridge (B) for a change in pace and dynamics
suitable for songs that want to showcase dynamic vocal and instrumental performances

struct_suggs.name: The Reversed Structure
attrs: has a unique structure starting with an intro (I) followed by a chorus (C1)
incorporates a prechorus (PC1 and PC2) and multiple verses (V1 and V2) before and after the second chorus (C2)
offers a bridge (B) for a change in melody and tempo
suitable for songs that want to break away from traditional song structures

struct_suggs.name: The Musical Adventure
attrs: includes a prechorus (PC1 and PC2) before the first chorus (C1)
utilizes a bridge (B) to provide a dynamic change in the song
offers two instrumental sections (intro and solo) to showcase musical talents
suitable for songs that want to maintain a steady energy level throughout with moments of breaks and showcases

struct_suggs.name: The Bold Experiment
attrs: has a unique structure starting with an intro (I) followed by a verse (V1) and two choruses (C1 and C2)
includes a bridge (B) after the second chorus for a dynamic change before returning to the original chorus (C1 and C2)
offers a prechorus (PC1) before repeating the chorus, adding variation to the song
suitable for songs with a strong chorus and a catchy melody.

Intro:
you had me twisted, wrung me out 'til i was dry,
and now i'm just like eatin' dirty earthworms, tryna survive.

Verse 1:
come on, let's make moves now, no time to delay,
all eyes on me, i'm rockin' the style today.
the monster don is in the building, can't you see?
so i read all the signs, that's how they down with me.
you need to return to an open state of mind,
all i wanna do is just be and unwind.
my flows go for miles, unstoppable,
take a dive in these bars, we can feel the miracles,

Pre-Chorus 1:
my secrets stay with me, won't let them out,
mama mama mama, that's what life is all about.

Chorus 1:
let it pour, let it rain,
but you still need some aid to ease the pain.
he gonna knock you off with his diamonds blingin',
two potato, but you gotta keep strong and keep swingin'.

Verse 2:
i like it when you keep on checking in,
but that drink starts to get on my last nerve again.
i don't give a damn, 'bout your fancy mansion,
in your pillowed house, with no love or passion.
this is the end, it's done, it's through,
but i'll always love you girls, you know it's true.
we shoot to kill, and we won't stop
until the blood spills, and we reach the top.

Chorus 2:
locked up in jail like it's my new job,
but i know you'll still be my fan when i'm out, no sob.
you say you a youngin, looking for fame and fortune,
but when shit gets rough, do you have the balls to pursue it?

Bridge:
they hear how i rhyme, they know i'm on the come up,
that lil bitch gotta earn it if she wanna get a number.
they see my shine, they wanna bask,
but you're already done, why are you still asking for a task?

Outro:
so this is it, it's do or die
we stay strapped like shit chrome, reaching for the sky.

Solo:
got a plaque on the wall, but it don't mean a thing,
'cause if i'm cheating, my heart still sings,

Instrumental:
you turned me into a freak, i can't even lie,
and this money got me feeling like we can't be denied.

Intro:
bitch, i know what you're about,
takin' all my money, ain't no doubt,

Verse 1:
don't give me those fake kicks, it's a no- go,
they're just soaking wet, like they danced in snow.
i'll chill under the jeweled moon until i'm calm,
scrolling through my phone, trying to find a balm,
but nobody knows me, what's truly inside,
these demons i battle, i do it alone, no guide.
my reputation spread like wildfire,
but you left me lonely, stuck at sixteen, lookin' for a savior.

Pre-Chorus 1:
listen close, take my ears and hear my sound,
put it down like me, ooh, we'll get around.

Chorus 1:
watch out for who's in charge, they'll try to deceive,
you gotta aim high and always believe.
i swear i put my life on the line, i put it on my soul,
but i'm still stuck, scrolling through my phone,

Verse 2:
you may not approve of the way we get down,
but it's just how it is, you stopped her from runnin' around.
age ain't nothing but a number, don't you know?
they'll lock you up for life, no questions, just like a recruiter.
counting all this cash, it's stacked in my bed,
but we still gotta handle business when midnight comes, bet,
my man won't stop, gotta take a break but my butt won't let.
ride sally, tell me where we headed,

Chorus 2:
the sun in my eyes, makes it hard to see,
but that glare ain't got nothin' on this rhinestone on my ralph lauren tee.
your girl in love with a boss, ain't no doubt
he say i ride real good, i'll wear that route.

Bridge:
keep it cool and chill, we need some extra room,
but still send shots, we ain't afraid of the boom.
i still think of you, even though we're through,
but you want to play, acting brand new.

Outro:
just look in my eyes, you'll see the pain that lies,
'cause you're not like those other girls, no need for disguise,

Solo:
can't come in this section if you ain't got that edge,
girl you know i count my racks up, chasing dreams until i'm dead.

Instrumental:
watch out, who's gonna feel the sharp bite of my blade,
you can keep dreaming, but reality's here, it won't fade.

Intro:
you wanna act like you're the boss in town?
so get up, get down, let's see who wears the crown.

Verse 1:
my rep got bigger, everyone knows my name,
but why should i trust myself, am i just playing a game?
take one look, see your true colors
talking like broads, you too petty, all busters.
i hate that you're leaving, wish you could stay,
let me rap it out, spittin' it this way,
this situation's just too absurd, i gotta say.
feeling like i'm stuck in a pickle,

Pre-Chorus 1:
all his boys are in a clique, they tight,
but he only got eyes for his tiger, she's his forever ride or die.

Chorus 1:
i know what's right and what's wrong, but sometimes i need to rest,
just give me a moment of quiet, a break from this constant test.
yo, turn that off, we don't wanna hear that noise,
are you waiting for someone to make some real noise?

Verse 2:
holding hands, we got the gangsta walk on lock,
but there's always someone who despises, trying to knock us off the block.
you a dancer, movin' so smooth,
she might be a capper, but she gotta stay true,
i feel sorry for them niggas, not knowing what we do.
listen to me before you leave, you hear?
these angry kids don't know nothin', just fear.
bom ba doo boo, you know that's my catchphrase,

Chorus 2:
i made a fortune, can't even believe it,
adam in the garden, now she acting all romantic, bring it.
your negative energy killing my vibe
dip and swish, gotta stay alive.

Bridge:
suckin' til she can't no more, that's how she pleases,
said it in a book, i believe in all of her thesis,
you get what you want, yeah, when you do it with finesse.
why you got me sweatin' you, always consistently,

Outro:
can i hear me a little bit louder, i said?
my man stood up for me, he's the best i ever had.

Solo:
whoa, my baby got me feeling some type of way,
but even with her, my life's still in disarray.

Instrumental:
panties on the floor, shining gold like i'm a miner,
all i wanna do is be down with this girl behind her.

Verse 1:
we run this game legit, no fake moves,
but if they cross us, we make sure they lose.
this girl's got me losing my mind,
she's an extraordinary girl, one of a kind.
let's put aside our egos, and just vibe,
ain't no riches or diamonds, that can make me feel alive.
she got it goin' on, make me wanna storm the shore,
she keepin' it wet, like a tsunami, can't ignore.

Pre-Chorus 1:
we'll ride it 'til the wheels fall off, or maybe just until dawn breaks,
and we gotta be real with it, no time for fakes.

Chorus 1:
got my new four, ain't giving it away
keep it real, give me some more, add that catchy hook and we'll play.
you drained me dry, left me hanging,
now we coming for vengeance, it's past eleven.

Verse 2:
got my girl with me, she's my number one
groovin' to the bass, dodging six shots like we're on the run.
if you keep pushing, i might just snap,
you remember when you promised to ride, now's your time to act.
we live for the rush, we crave the thrill,
and when we high, it's like time stands still,
and we like it wow!! so we spray paint our names on government buildings until we get our fill.
i know i mess up every single damn day,

Chorus 2:
and i stay on top, still runnin' this game,
thinking 'bout the things that i wouldn't mind doing with you, shame.
my ego bigger than the sun, you gotta admit
step to me wrong and you'll end up in the dirt, that's it.

Bridge:
my voice is my weapon, it's my truth,
and i got that same mission, it's what i pursue.
i don't need no loan, i get it back in two days
let it sink in, i'm livin' lavish in my own way.

Outro:
open your eyes and see what's true,
they say i'm cheating but they don't know the truth,

Solo:
it's never gonna stop, the violence won't decrease,
and i'll kill any man with a gun like a gay bitch, peace.

Instrumental:
always got a new four on my side,
and every track's got that catchy hook that we ride.

Intro:
i'm out here dream chasing while they stuck in their dimension,
if you ain't real, you can't step in our section.

Verse 1:
gimme that encore, we can't get enough,
every verse got that catchy hook that's tough.
we see each other clear, no need for words
we can detect all the lies, our vision blurred.
i'm an uptown nigga, livin' life in luxury
and the house got 5 more, watchin' my back like it's their duty.
always looking like one of those nights, living in my own little world
got my own style, ain't no drama unfurled

Pre-Chorus 1:
they say i speak for us millennials, our voices will prevail,
but that girl you're with, she can't love you like i will.

Chorus 1:
i move in silence, like i'm snowden, gotta stay lowkey,
two tone on my wrist, so i can learn your location, discreetly.
hey baby, you gotta be strong,
'cause this life we're living, it's a marathon, not a sprint, so bump all these songs.

Verse 2:
my boy chief keef, yeah we hustlin' together,
so when it all gets too much, take me away and we'll disappear forever.
it's all just corporate art, we're just a number in their eyes,
eating dirty earthworms, while they feast on caviar and fries,
take me to portugal, where we can be free to roam and rise.
ain't nothin' better than dancing with my lady,
a man did it long time ago, and i'll keep it going, maybe.
too much to say, but i won't waste the words,

Chorus 2:
you'll never have to question my loyalty
i'll jump into the deep blue sea, if that's where you want me to be.
you may not like it, but i can't help how i feel,
maybe we were crazy, but our love was too real,

Bridge:
let me spit it like this, it's so outrageous
we do it because we can, we're courageous.
we've been down since day 1, never changed, stayed real,
and everything we do always makes you feel.

Outro:
got all these goofies hatin', they can't handle our love,
my bitch amazon, she fly like a dove,

Solo:
she a classy lady, ain't nothin' basic,
gonna keep it spacious in our love oasis,

Instrumental:
he saw the storm brewing up above,
and he gonna teach y'all suckas a thing or two, show you some love.

Intro:
if it were to crack below, we'd all fall apart
and wonder where it all went wrong, tryin' to mend our hearts.

Verse 1:
you know it's true now, greed takin' over our thoughts
money talks, we gotta put a stop to these wars.
this album's my art, i want them to see,
and my money's on point, just like a fresh perm,
got extra clips, don't give a damn about what you confirm.
listen straight, no lies or deceit,
gotta be real with it, can't handle no more defeat,
omenxiii, we bringin' the heat.

Pre-Chorus 1:
you think you know my future, but i'll show you different,
got the power to change, i'll make it shine like shimmerin'.

Chorus 1:
i can't imagine me livin' without you,
but i know life's a bitch and sometimes we gotta make do.
i'll do anything for you, my dear,
even if it means swallowing worms, my dear,

Verse 2:
i don't need no tricks, i wonder how i get the dope so cheap
sippin' that rum, livin' life like barbados beach
let me win your love, baby, we can do it plush.
gorilla in the kitchen, i just ate some chops,
doubling up on that cash, i'll never stop,
doing it all for y'all, you know i've got that spot.
count that money, stack it up high,
i'm tryna make myself heard before i die,

Chorus 2:
so take me away, where the music's loud and the lights are bright,
got her in darkness, she's my queen, i'm her knight,
so i'm doin' it for y'all, give you the gift of sight.
tearin' through this city, all alone i roam,

Bridge:
the gods know the deal, they can't front on this,
no matter what, we'll stick together, from day 1 to the abyss.
can you turn me up a little louder, i wanna feel the beat,
when your arms wrap around me, i get lost and can't retreat.

Solo:
i hold your future in my hands, better believe,
if i said i saw your god, would you still deceive?

Instrumental:
call me by my true name, no tricks up my sleeve,
and you can taste this pussy, you'll never leave.
